question.title: Java TIMED_WAITING and Tomcat server not responsing

node.contents: So in your opinion there is nothing wrong with the threads states and the casue of tomcat not processing requests is due to something else? If that is the case any pointers where i can begin looking as i have already increased the maxThread in tomcat.

node.contents: The threads there are idle just waiting for a scheduled task's time to be up. For instance if I submit a task to run once every 10 seconds, the time it's spent waiting for the 10 seconds to tick, it will sit on that queue. So I don't think anything is moving slowly because of that

node.contents: Hi I have an application which sometimes responds to requests but sometimes doest recieve request on the given port. This appears to be a capacity issue as traffic has increased. Now I can't tell what is making in choke and since they are very many parameters to adjust, i decided to look at thread dump from jstack.
